# Feature Flag Rules

## Where Flags Are Defined
- `config/config.toml` under `[default.features]`
- Flags are boolean values with defaults shipped to production

## Key Feature Flags
```toml
[default.features]
generate_report     = false   # CSV/report generation
mixpanel            = false   # Analytics/tracking
feedback            = false   # User feedback widget
test_processors     = true    # Test payment processors
recon               = false   # Reconciliation module
payout              = true    # Disbursement flows
frm                 = true    # Fraud & Risk Management
sample_data         = false   # Demo/sample data mode
audit_trail         = true    # Audit log visibility
test_live_toggle    = false   # Toggle between test/live mode
is_live_mode        = false   # Live vs sandbox mode
email               = false   # Email notification features
surcharge           = true    # Surcharge on payments
branding            = false   # White-label branding
totp                = true    # TOTP 2FA
threeds_authenticator = true  # 3DS authentication
```

## How Flags Are Consumed
- Flags are exposed at runtime via `window.__env__` through the JS interop layer
- Components read flags through the feature flag Recoil atom or React context in `src/`
- Do **not** import or read `config.toml` directly from ReScript components

## Rules
- **Never flip defaults** in `config/config.toml` — use environment variable overrides for local dev
- To enable a flag locally: set env var `default__features__<flag_name>=true`
- For production flag changes: update deployment config, not `config.toml` defaults
- New flags must be added to `config.toml` and the feature flag type/context in `src/`
